<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="324" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[160,1156,454,1104]" pageId="13" pageNumber="324">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,268,454,480]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="324">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Thorne G &amp; Swanger HH" box="[285,604,455,480]" pageId="13" pageNumber="324" pagination="223" refId="ref19695" refString="Thorne G, Swanger HH. 1936. A monograph of the nematode genera Dorylaimus Dujardin, Aporcelaimus n. g., Dorylaimoides n. g., and Pungentus n. g. Cap Zoologica. 6: 223." type="journal article" year="1936">Thorne and Swanger (1936)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thorne and Swanger" authorityYear="1936" box="[733,971,455,480]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="13" pageNumber="324" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="parvus">
<emphasis box="[733,971,455,480]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="324">Dorylaimoides parvus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on 
<specimenCount pageId="13" pageNumber="324" type="female">eight females</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount box="[302,432,489,514]" pageId="13" pageNumber="324" type="male">three males</specimenCount>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[499,562,489,514]" name="Brazil" pageId="13" pageNumber="324">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Loof PAA" box="[571,697,489,514]" pageId="13" pageNumber="324" pagination="201 - 300" refId="ref19015" refString="Loof PAA. 1964. Free-living and plant-parasitic nematodes from Venezuela. Nematologica. 10 (2): 201 - 300. doi: 10.1163 / 187529264 X 00042." type="journal article" year="1964">Loof (1964)</bibRefCitation>
redescribed this species from 
<collectingCountry box="[1035,1153,489,514]" name="Venezuela" pageId="13" pageNumber="324">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Goseco CG &amp; Ferris VR &amp; Ferris JM" box="[160,395,524,549]" pageId="13" pageNumber="324" refId="ref18466" refString="Goseco CG, Ferris VR, Ferris JM. 1976. Revision in Leptonchoidea (Nematoda: Dorylaimida). Dorylaimoides in Dorylaimoididae, Dorylaimoididinae, Calolaimus and Timmus n. gen. in Dorylaimoididae, Calolaiminae, and Miranema in Mirannematidae. Res. Bull., Agric. Expt. Sta., Purdue Univ., West Lafayette No. 941; p. 46." type="journal volume" year="1976">Goseco et al. (1976)</bibRefCitation>
, in their revision of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thorne and Swanger" authorityYear="1936" box="[767,922,524,549]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="13" pageNumber="324" phylum="Nematoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[767,922,524,549]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="324">Dorylaimoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, restudied the 
<typeStatus box="[1105,1155,524,549]" pageId="13" pageNumber="324">type</typeStatus>
specimens as well as the Venezuelan specimens. 
<bibRefCitation author="Jana A &amp; Baqri QH" box="[719,965,559,584]" pageId="13" pageNumber="324" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref18975" refString="Jana A, Baqri QH. 1981. Nematodes from West Bengal (India) XI. Studies on the species of the superfamily Leptonchoidea (Dorylaimida). J Zoo Soc Ind. 33: 1 - 24." type="journal article" year="1981">Jana and Baqri (1981)</bibRefCitation>
reported it from 
<collectingCountry box="[160,218,593,618]" name="India" pageId="13" pageNumber="324">India</collectingCountry>
. The morphometrics of the present population conforms well with the 
<typeStatus box="[1012,1062,593,618]" pageId="13" pageNumber="324">type</typeStatus>
population except in having a slightly less slender body (a = 32–37 vs 37–58) and lower b (5.3–6.1 vs 6.1–7.5) and c (7.9–9.7 vs 10–13) ratios. The present specimens also conform well with the 
<collectingCountry box="[207,322,697,722]" name="Venezuela" pageId="13" pageNumber="324">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
specimens except in having smaller spicules (28–32 vs 34–36 µm). The present population also conforms well with the Indian population except in having a slightly shorter body (L = 0.9–1.2 vs 
<quantity box="[597,729,767,792]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="13" pageNumber="324" unit="mm" value="1.35" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.2">1.2–1.5 mm</quantity>
) and lower b (5.3–6.1 vs 6.7–8.0) and c (7.9–9.7 vs 11–14) ratios. These differences are considered intraspecific variability.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[160,1156,454,1104]" pageId="13" pageNumber="324">
In the presence of an elongated tail, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thorne and Swanger" authorityYear="1936" box="[632,871,836,861]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="13" pageNumber="324" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="parvus">
<emphasis box="[632,871,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="324">Dorylaimoides parvus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Siddiqi, 1965" authorityName="Siddiqi" authorityYear="1965" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="13" pageNumber="324" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="elaboratus">
<emphasis box="[1007,1155,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="324">D. elaboratus</emphasis>
Siddiqi, 1965
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Meyl, 1956" authorityName="Meyl" authorityYear="1956" box="[371,681,871,896]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="13" pageNumber="324" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="paulbuchneri">
<emphasis box="[371,547,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="324">D. paulbuchneri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Meyl AH" box="[557,681,871,896]" pageId="13" pageNumber="324" pagination="311 - 325" refId="ref19046" refString="Meyl AH. 1956. Beitrge zur freilebenden nematodenfauna Brasiliens, I. Achth eue nematodenarten der Uberfamilie Dorylaimoidea. Nematologica. 1 (4): 311 - 325. doi: 10.1163 / 187529256 X 00320." type="journal article" year="1956">Meyl, 1956</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but it differs from the former in having differently shaped spicules (slender, slightly curved ventrally vs robust, more curved ventrally) and first ventromedian supplements located beyond the range of the spicules (vs first ventromedian supplements located within the range of the spicules).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[160,1156,454,1104]" pageId="13" pageNumber="324">
From 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meyl" authorityYear="1956" box="[259,434,1009,1034]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="13" pageNumber="324" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="paulbuchneri">
<emphasis box="[259,434,1009,1034]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="324">D. paulbuchneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it differs in having labial papillae indistinct (vs distinct); differently shaped odontostyle (slender vs robust) and differently shaped spicules (slender, slightly curved ventrally vs robust, more ventrally curved).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
